Add Role class for student/tutor distinction
commitResults.messageBody:
The system needs to differentiate between students and tutors
to support tuition centre management features.

This commit introduces a Role class that:
* Validates role input to accept only 'student' or 'tutor'
* Stores role in lowercase for consistency
* Follows the same pattern as other Person attributes (Phone, Email)
* Provides clear error message for invalid role entries

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Class entity for tuition centre class management
commitResults.messageBody:
Students and tutors need to be associated with classes they
attend or teach, formatted with level, day, and time.

This commit introduces a Class class that:
* Validates class format: s[1-5][day][time] (e.g., s4mon1600)
* Supports standard week days (mon-sun)
* Enforces 24-hour time format (0000-2359)
* Stores class in lowercase for consistency
* Will support multiple classes per person via Set<Class>

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Phone validation to require exactly 8 digits
commitResults.messageBody:
Generic phone validation (3+ digits) allows invalid entries
that don't match Singapore phone number format.

This commit updates Phone validation to:
* Require exactly 8 digits for Singapore phone numbers
* Update error message to reflect Singapore number requirement
* Prevent invalid phone numbers like '123' or '123456789'

commitResults.messageTitle: Add PREFIX_ROLE and PREFIX_CLASS to CliSyntax
commitResults.messageBody:
The add command needs to support role (r/) and class (c/) prefixes
for the new student/tutor management features.

This commit adds:
* PREFIX_ROLE for r/ prefix
* PREFIX_CLASS for c/ prefix
These will be used in command parsing to identify role and class
parameters from user input.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Role and Class fields to Person entity
commitResults.messageBody:
Person needs to be extended to support student/tutor roles
and associated class information for tuition centre management.

This commit updates Person class to:
* Add Role field to distinguish between students and tutors
* Add Set<Class> to support multiple classes per person
* Update constructor to accept role and classes parameters
* Add getRole() and getClasses() getter methods
* Update equals(), hashCode(), and toString() to include new fields
* Update isSamePerson() to check both name AND phone for duplicates
  (allows siblings with same name but different phone numbers)

commitResults.messageTitle: Add parseRole and parseClasses to ParserUtil
commitResults.messageBody:
AddCommandParser needs utility methods to parse role and class
parameters from user input strings.

This commit adds to ParserUtil:
* parseRole() - parses and validates role strings
* parseClass() - parses and validates individual class strings
* parseClasses() - parses collection of class strings into Set<Class>
All methods follow the same pattern as existing parse methods
(parseName, parsePhone, etc.) with trimming and validation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update AddCommandParser for role and class support
commitResults.messageBody:
AddCommandParser needs to parse the new role and class parameters
and make address optional per feature requirements.

This commit updates AddCommandParser to:
* Import PREFIX_ROLE and PREFIX_CLASS constants
* Import Role and Class entity classes
* Add role and class to tokenization
* Require role (r/) as mandatory field (student/tutor)
* Require at least one class (c/) - validate non-empty
* Make address (a/) optional (defaults to '-' placeholder)
* Update Person constructor call with all new parameters
* Add @Override annotation for consistency
* Fix formatting (blank lines after imports)

Command format now: add r/{role} n/{name} p/{phone} e/{email} [a/{address}] c/{class} [c/{class}]...

commitResults.messageTitle: Update AddCommand messages for student/tutor system
commitResults.messageBody:
Success and error messages need to reflect the new student/tutor
role-based system instead of generic 'person' terminology.

This commit updates AddCommand to:
* Add PREFIX_ROLE and PREFIX_CLASS imports
* Update MESSAGE_USAGE with new command format including role and class
* Update example to show student with multiple classes
* Change success message to: 'Student/Tutor {name} added successfully'
* Capitalize role in success message for better display
* Update duplicate message to reference student/tutor
* Remove unused Messages import

Example output: 'Student kevin added successfully'

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix compilation errors for new Person constructor
commitResults.messageBody:
The Person constructor was updated to include Role and Set<Class>,
which broke existing code that used the old constructor signature.

This commit fixes all compilation errors by:
* Update EditCommand to preserve role and classes when editing
* Update JsonAdaptedPerson to serialize/deserialize role and classes
* Create JsonAdaptedClass for JSON serialization of Class objects
* Update SampleDataUtil with sample students and tutors with classes
* Update PersonBuilder test utility to include role and classes
* Update JsonAdaptedPersonTest to use new constructor signature

All files now compile successfully with the new Person model.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix all tests for new Person model with role and classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Tests were failing due to Person constructor changes and new
validation rules (8-digit phone, role, classes required).

This commit updates all test files to:
* Add withRole() and withClasses() methods to PersonBuilder
* Update TypicalPersons with valid 8-digit phones, roles, and classes
* Add VALID_ROLE, VALID_CLASS constants to CommandTestUtil
* Add INVALID_ROLE, INVALID_CLASS test cases
* Fix AddCommandTest success message format (role + name)
* Fix PhoneTest validation (exactly 8 digits, not 3+)
* Fix PersonTest isSamePerson() to check name AND phone
* Update PersonUtil.getPersonDetails() to include role and classes
* Update all JSON test data files with role and classes fields
* Fix AddCommandParserTest with role and class in all test commands
* Fix LogicManagerTest to include role and class in add command
* Remove unused imports
